  print("{{also|Balls}}\n==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/b\u0254\u02d0lz/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-balls.ogg|Audio (US)}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-balls.ogg|Audio (UK)}}\n* {{rhymes|en|\u0254\u02d0lz|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|en|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|en|ball}}\n#: {{ux|en|Can you believe he can juggle six '''balls''' at once?}}\n#* {{rfdate|en}} {{w|W. S. Gilbert}}, ''{{w|HMS Pinafore}}''\n#*: When the '''balls''' whistle free o'er the bright blue sea / We stand to our guns all day.\n# {{lb|en|vulgar|colloquial}} The [[testicles]].\n#: {{ux|en|After that shot, his '''balls''' were really hurting!}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|vulgar|colloquial}} [[masculinity|Masculinity]], [[particularly]] [[strength]], [[courage]], and [[force of will]]; [[chutzpah]]; [[brazenness]].\n#* '''2007 September 28''', Graham Linehan, ''{{w|The IT Crowd}}'', Season 2, Episode 6:\n#*: ''Douglas:'' You've got [[spunk]]. And '''balls'''. And I like that in a woman.\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:courage}}\n#: {{ux|en|He must have a lot of '''balls''' to talk to his boss that way.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He's the guy with the big '''balls''' in that group.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Balls''' is all that it takes to succeed.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Where the Air is Clear| page=80| url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1564783448| author=Carlos Fuentes, Sam Hileman| year=1960| passage='''Balls''' is all it takes to handle these people}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Havana Blue|page=137| url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1904738222| author=Leonardo Padura| year=2006| passage=\u201c'''Balls''', gentlemen, '''balls''' is what you need to win at this game\"}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|Britain|Ireland|Australia|New Zealand|South Africa|vulgar|colloquial }} {{synonym of|en|bollocks}}, {{ngd|nonsense}}.\n#: {{ux|en|That's a load of '''balls'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK|Ireland|Australia| New Zealand|South Africa|vulgar}} A [[balls-up]]; a [[botch]]ed job.\n#: {{ux|en|Don't make a '''balls''' of it!}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{der-top}}\n* {{l|en|ballsy}}\n* {{l|en|bust one's balls}}\n* {{l|en|bust someone's balls}}\n*{{vern|cramp balls}} ({{taxlink|Daldinia concentrica|species|ver=220116}})\n* {{l|en|have someone by the balls}}\n{{der-bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-see|follow the translations in the entry \"ball\"|ball}}\n\n{{trans-top|slang for testicles}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|\u0571\u057e\u0565\u0580|p}}, {{t+|hy|\u057a\u056c\u0578\u0580}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|coalji|n-p}}, {{t|rup|boashi|f-p}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|g\u00fcevos|m-p}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|da\u015f\u015faq}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|\u09ac\u09c0\u099a\u09bf}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|\u0442\u043e\u043f\u043a\u0438|f-p}}, {{t|bg|\u0442\u0430\u0448\u0430\u0446\u0438|m-p}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|collons|m-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|\u6ce2\u5b50|tr=bo1 zi2}}, {{qualifier|vulgar}} {{t|yue|\u6625\u5b50|tr=ceon1 zi2}}, {{t|yue|\u6ce2\u73e0|tr=bo1 zyu1}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|koule|f-p}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|testikler|c-p}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kojono|alt=kojonoj}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|munad|p}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|pallit|p}}, {{t+|fi|munat|p}}, {{t+|fi|kassit|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|couilles|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|burnes|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|roustons|m-p}}, {{t+|fr|balloches|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|valseuses|f-p}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|coll\u00f3ns|m-p}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|\u10e7\u10d5\u10d4\u10e0\u10d4\u10d1\u10d8|sc=Geor}}, {{t|ka|\u10d9\u10d5\u10d0\u10ef\u10d4\u10d1\u10d8|sc=Geor}}, {{t|ka|\u10e7\u10dd\u10e7\u10dd\u10e0\u10d4\u10d1\u10d8|sc=Geor}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Eier|p}}, {{t+|de|Kl\u00f6ten|p|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|\u03b1\u03c1\u03c7\u03af\u03b4\u03b9\u03b1|n-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|\u05d1\u05d9\u05e6\u05d9\u05dd|p|tr=betzim}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|t\u00f6k}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|peler}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}, {{t|id|biji salak}}, {{t|id|biji peler}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|coleones}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|balle|f-p}}, {{t+|it|palle|f-p}}, {{t+|it|coglioni|m-p}}, {{t+|it|testicoli|m-p}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|\u91d1\